The paper presents a new language model for concurrent software based on communicating processes, which involves programming paradigms related to programming languages (PL) and software engineering (SE). The paper also discusses a static analysis that guarantees compatibility, which is related to distributed computing (DC) and logic in computer science (LO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of connectors and choreographies, which are related to systems and control (SY).
